# zensim-gpu cached-ref vs. pair-mode bench metadata
# Commit: TBD (filled at commit time)
# Host: water-cooled AMD Ryzen 9 7950X, 128 GB RAM, RTX 5070 (driver 596.21, CUDA 13.2)
# Date: 2026-05-22
# Backends: cubecl-wgpu (WSL2 Vulkan) and cubecl-cuda
# Command: cargo bench --no-default-features \
#            --features "cubecl-types,<wgpu|cuda>,pixels,fast-reduction" \
#            -p zensim-gpu --bench cached_ref
#
# Columns:
#   mode: "pair_mode" (compute_features_vec_srgb_u8) or "cached_ref"
#         (set_reference_srgb_u8 + compute_with_reference_srgb_u8 × N)
#   backend: cuda / wgpu
#   w / h: image dimensions
#   n_dist: number of distortions per reference (sweep-style workload)
#   mean_ms: mean wall-clock for N_DIST distortions (one set_reference
#            + N_DIST scores for cached, N_DIST × (set+score) for pair)
#   mad_ms: median absolute deviation
#   ci95_lo / ci95_hi: 95% confidence interval (zenbench reports only
#                     when CV is high enough to warrant it; blank where
#                     zenbench didn't print it)
#   cv_pct: coefficient of variation across iters (zenbench summary)
#
# Headline: cached path saves ~40% wall-clock on a 10-distortions-per-ref
# sweep workload at 1024² on both wgpu and CUDA. Matches the prediction
# of "skip N-1 ref uploads + N-1 ref-pyramid kernel launches".
#
# Reproduce on a clean GPU:
#   cargo bench --no-default-features \
#     --features "cubecl-types,cuda,pixels,fast-reduction" \
#     -p zensim-gpu --bench cached_ref
